 to the Galactic center\nthan previously thought, with Terzan10 being on the far side of the Galactic\nbulge. Finally, we discuss their Oosterhoff properties, and conclude that both\nclusters stand out from the dichotomy followed by most Galactic globular\nclusters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Nov 2014 18:41:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Nov 2014 18:57:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
