{"id":"1411.1803","submitter":"Mario Ponce","authors":"Pilar Herreros, Mario Ponce and J.J.P Veerman","title":"Regularity of Mediatrices in Surfaces","comments":"9 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For distinct points $p$ and $q$ in a two-dimensional Riemannian manifold, one\ndefines their mediatrix $L_{pq}$ as the set of equidistant points to $p$ and\n$q$. It is known that mediatrices have a cell decomposition consisting of a\nfinite number of branch points connected by Lipschitz curves. This paper\nestablishes additional geometric regularity properties of mediatrices. We show\nthat mediatrices have the radial linearizability property, which implies that\nat each point they have a geometrically defined derivative in the branching\ndirections. Also, we study the particular case of mediatrices on spheres, by\nshowing that they are Lipschitz simple closed curves exhibiting at most\ncountably many singularities, with finite total angular deficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Nov 2014 00:40:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-10"}
